title: [Western Waterway, Charl's Teeth]
description: The monstrous black obsidian cliffs to the west all but obscure the sky.  Seabirds circle the enormous heights, occasionally settling along the ragged edges of the stones.  Blue-green water splashes and sloshes below, never at rest, never at peace, its sound as insistent as the mournful cries of the aerial creatures that sail and glide overhead.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, southeast, south, northwest
